\title{family of sets}
\date{2024-01-31}
\author{jonmsterling}
\taxon{definition}

\import{jms-00JB}

\p{A \dem{family of sets} indexed in a set #{I} is defined to be a set #{S} equipped with a [function](jms-00KF) #{\pi_S\colon S \to I}. For #{i\in I}, we will write #{S_i\subseteq S} for the [inverse image](jms-00N7) #{\inv-img{\pi_S}{\brc{i}}\subseteq S}:}

##{
 \begin{aligned}
  S_i
  &=
  \inv-img{\pi_S}{\brc{i}}
  \\
  &=
  \compr{s\in S}{\forall j\in I\punctdot s\mathrel{\pi_S} j \implies j\in\brc{i}}
  \\
  &=
  \compr{s\in S}{\forall j\in I\punctdot \pi_S\prn{s}=j \implies j=i}
  \\
  &=
  \compr{s\in S}{\pi_S\prn{s}=j}
 \end{aligned}
}

\p{Thus #{S} is the disjoint union of all the #{S_i}.}
